						<div class="postbody">Sorry for hijacking this thread, but:<div class="quotetitle">bigjt_2 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So "sprites," as in other video game programming, are basically graphics (in this case 8x8 or 8x16 tiles) that <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline">animate</span></strong>, move, or may require some collision detection.  And background tiles would basically be everything else.  Am I correct in my understanding of that?</div>If a tile is animated yet it is stationary with the scrolling, it could also be in the background instead of being a sprite, right?</div>

